WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.900 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.900 --> 00:00:04.050 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:04.050 --> 00:00:05.595 align:middle line:90%
>> The Templars in Brazil.

00:00:05.595 --> 00:00:11.150 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.150 --> 00:00:14.900 align:middle line:10%
This is the story of
Dr. Kathleen Ball,

00:00:14.900 --> 00:00:20.120 align:middle line:10%
researcher, traveler, and
explorer of ancient sites

00:00:20.120 --> 00:00:22.310 align:middle line:10%
and her discovery of a cave--

00:00:22.310 --> 00:00:25.050 align:middle line:10%
>> Woo!

00:00:25.050 --> 00:00:28.740 align:middle line:84%
>> --a cave hidden in a
remote area on the outskirts

00:00:28.740 --> 00:00:37.660 align:middle line:84%
of a small Brazilian town,
a cave that was carved

00:00:37.660 --> 00:00:39.025 align:middle line:90%
by the Knights Templar.

00:00:39.025 --> 00:00:43.190 align:middle line:90%


00:00:43.190 --> 00:00:45.980 align:middle line:84%
We will explore how
this adventure began

00:00:45.980 --> 00:00:48.890 align:middle line:84%
and the little-known history
of the Templars' travels

00:00:48.890 --> 00:00:51.500 align:middle line:90%
to Brazil.

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:54.290 align:middle line:84%
What were their reasons
for coming to South America

00:00:54.290 --> 00:00:58.025 align:middle line:84%
two centuries before Columbus
sailed to the new world?

00:00:58.025 --> 00:01:00.650 align:middle line:90%


00:01:00.650 --> 00:01:03.850 align:middle line:84%
We'll also investigate
the Templars' agenda.

00:01:03.850 --> 00:01:06.920 align:middle line:84%
What goals did they have
for medieval society?

00:01:06.920 --> 00:01:09.770 align:middle line:90%


00:01:09.770 --> 00:01:13.100 align:middle line:10%
And we'll find out how
Kathleen Ball's exploration

00:01:13.100 --> 00:01:16.730 align:middle line:10%
of a dungeon in Domme, France,
where many Templars were

00:01:16.730 --> 00:01:19.750 align:middle line:10%
imprisoned in the
early 14th century,

00:01:19.750 --> 00:01:25.210 align:middle line:10%
sheds light on her life-altering
and history-changing discovery.

00:01:25.210 --> 00:01:37.820 align:middle line:90%


00:01:37.820 --> 00:01:41.810 align:middle line:10%
>> My name is Kathleen Ball,
and I'm here in Alto Paraíso

00:01:41.810 --> 00:01:43.100 align:middle line:10%
Brazil.

00:01:43.100 --> 00:01:47.600 align:middle line:84%
And this is my third trip here,
and we have been on the hunt

00:01:47.600 --> 00:01:51.290 align:middle line:84%
for history relating
to the Templars.

00:01:51.290 --> 00:01:54.280 align:middle line:90%
>> August 2015.

00:01:54.280 --> 00:01:56.890 align:middle line:84%
During a hiking trip through
Brazil with a friend,

00:01:56.890 --> 00:02:02.560 align:middle line:84%
Adele Goode, Kathleen visits
the tiny town of Alto Paraíso.

00:02:02.560 --> 00:02:05.950 align:middle line:84%
She chances upon an
exquisite, secluded area

00:02:05.950 --> 00:02:08.970 align:middle line:90%
in the Chapada National Park.

00:02:08.970 --> 00:02:11.760 align:middle line:84%
Surrounded by
breathtaking waterfalls

00:02:11.760 --> 00:02:14.790 align:middle line:84%
and unique megalithic
rock formations,

00:02:14.790 --> 00:02:18.730 align:middle line:84%
it feels like a
place out of time.

00:02:18.730 --> 00:02:22.750 align:middle line:84%
There, the unspoiled natural
beauty of the landscape

00:02:22.750 --> 00:02:27.730 align:middle line:84%
mirrors the quiet dignity and
uncomplicated lifestyle enjoyed

00:02:27.730 --> 00:02:30.530 align:middle line:90%
by the local population.

00:02:30.530 --> 00:02:33.200 align:middle line:84%
Charmed, Kathleen
and Adele decide

00:02:33.200 --> 00:02:38.480 align:middle line:84%
to rent rooms in a local inn, or
posada, and explore the region.

00:02:38.480 --> 00:02:41.950 align:middle line:90%


00:02:41.950 --> 00:02:45.760 align:middle line:84%
On a hike to Agua Fria, a
waterfall some five miles

00:02:45.760 --> 00:02:48.760 align:middle line:84%
outside of town, a
local man tells them

00:02:48.760 --> 00:02:52.010 align:middle line:84%
about something unusual
on an adjacent property.

00:02:52.010 --> 00:02:53.530 align:middle line:90%
[WATER RUSHING]

00:02:53.530 --> 00:02:57.220 align:middle line:84%
He describes a vein
of quartz crystal rock

00:02:57.220 --> 00:03:00.280 align:middle line:84%
two feet wide and stretching
across the landscape

00:03:00.280 --> 00:03:02.790 align:middle line:90%
for roughly two miles.

00:03:02.790 --> 00:03:06.540 align:middle line:84%
He asks the women if they
would like to see it.

00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:10.200 align:middle line:84%
Both Kathleen and Adele agree
that it sounds intriguing,

00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:12.780 align:middle line:90%
and they set off.

00:03:12.780 --> 00:03:16.290 align:middle line:84%
Neither has any idea
that they are soon

00:03:16.290 --> 00:03:19.710 align:middle line:84%
to make an extraordinary
discovery, one that

00:03:19.710 --> 00:03:23.680 align:middle line:84%
will forever transform history's
understanding of the Knights

00:03:23.680 --> 00:03:24.480 align:middle line:90%
Templar.

00:03:24.480 --> 00:03:28.700 align:middle line:90%


00:03:28.700 --> 00:03:31.880 align:middle line:84%
Kathleen and Adele follow
the vein of crystal for some

00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:36.830 align:middle line:84%
distance, eventually arriving
at a humble-looking cave nestled

00:03:36.830 --> 00:03:41.710 align:middle line:84%
into a nondescript hillside
outside of Alto Paraíso.

00:03:41.710 --> 00:03:45.380 align:middle line:84%
There, carved into
the cave wall,

00:03:45.380 --> 00:03:48.810 align:middle line:90%
Kathleen spots an engraving.

00:03:48.810 --> 00:03:54.720 align:middle line:84%
Unbelievably, it's a
distinctive Templar cross.

00:03:54.720 --> 00:03:56.520 align:middle line:84%
The cross is
striking to Kathleen

00:03:56.520 --> 00:04:00.990 align:middle line:84%
for a number of reasons, but
foremost among them is the fact

00:04:00.990 --> 00:04:04.570 align:middle line:84%
that the carving is
here in the first place.

00:04:04.570 --> 00:04:07.440 align:middle line:84%
After all, Kathleen
is thousands of miles

00:04:07.440 --> 00:04:10.170 align:middle line:84%
and an ocean away
from other Templar

00:04:10.170 --> 00:04:15.780 align:middle line:84%
crosses that she's seen
and studied in France.

00:04:15.780 --> 00:04:19.050 align:middle line:10%
Recognizing the potential
gravity of her finding,

00:04:19.050 --> 00:04:23.250 align:middle line:10%
Kathleen hastily takes several
pictures of the carving.

00:04:23.250 --> 00:04:26.280 align:middle line:84%
After she and Adele
return to their posada,

00:04:26.280 --> 00:04:30.120 align:middle line:84%
Kathleen decides that she
must dig deeper and explore

00:04:30.120 --> 00:04:34.170 align:middle line:84%
any potential links between
this carving in Brazil

00:04:34.170 --> 00:04:36.740 align:middle line:90%
and those in France.

00:04:36.740 --> 00:04:39.560 align:middle line:84%
But before she
leaves Alto Paraíso,

00:04:39.560 --> 00:04:43.220 align:middle line:84%
she also conducts a short
interview with Liomar,

00:04:43.220 --> 00:04:46.430 align:middle line:84%
a local resident
and their guide.

00:04:46.430 --> 00:04:49.670 align:middle line:84%
>> The slaves back then would
pan the crystals here and bring

00:04:49.670 --> 00:04:51.617 align:middle line:84%
them over to the
cavern to bless it.

00:04:51.617 --> 00:04:53.450 align:middle line:84%
And this is where they
would do the benzene,

00:04:53.450 --> 00:04:55.370 align:middle line:90%
at the cave temple.

00:04:55.370 --> 00:04:59.600 align:middle line:84%
Old times, the
times of the slaves,

00:04:59.600 --> 00:05:02.510 align:middle line:84%
the blacks and the time of
the quiolombola settlement.

00:05:02.510 --> 00:05:03.680 align:middle line:90%
>> Ah.

00:05:03.680 --> 00:05:05.454 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING PORTUGUESE]

00:05:05.454 --> 00:05:06.360 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:05:06.360 --> 00:05:07.160 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:05:07.160 --> 00:05:07.960 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:05:07.960 --> 00:05:09.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Perfecto.

00:05:09.310 --> 00:05:12.550 align:middle line:84%
>> Kathleen's immediate
recognition of the importance

00:05:12.550 --> 00:05:16.480 align:middle line:84%
of the Templar cross carved into
a cave wall near Alto Paraíso,

00:05:16.480 --> 00:05:21.760 align:middle line:84%
Brazil is rooted in a trip
she made to France six years

00:05:21.760 --> 00:05:23.950 align:middle line:90%
before.

00:05:23.950 --> 00:05:29.200 align:middle line:84%
In May of 2009, she visited
the fortified medieval town

00:05:29.200 --> 00:05:32.860 align:middle line:90%
of Domme in the Dordogne area.

00:05:32.860 --> 00:05:36.490 align:middle line:84%
She explored the little-known
and badly deteriorated dungeons

00:05:36.490 --> 00:05:38.920 align:middle line:90%
of the ancient town.

00:05:38.920 --> 00:05:42.490 align:middle line:10%
This is where hundreds
of Templar Knights

00:05:42.490 --> 00:05:48.480 align:middle line:10%
had been imprisoned by King
Phillip IV of France in 1307.

00:05:48.480 --> 00:05:54.210 align:middle line:84%
And there, on the dungeon walls,
were the remains of graffiti

00:05:54.210 --> 00:05:57.390 align:middle line:90%
carved by the jailed knights.

00:05:57.390 --> 00:06:01.620 align:middle line:84%
Doomed by the king to torture
and eventual execution,

00:06:01.620 --> 00:06:05.760 align:middle line:84%
they left behind numerous
glyphs of Templar crosses

00:06:05.760 --> 00:06:08.730 align:middle line:90%
indicative of their era.

00:06:08.730 --> 00:06:13.380 align:middle line:84%
During her visit, Kathleen
photographed these glyphs.

00:06:13.380 --> 00:06:17.520 align:middle line:84%
>> During my trip in
2009 to Domme, France,

00:06:17.520 --> 00:06:21.060 align:middle line:84%
my husband and I-- we had
gone there originally to see

00:06:21.060 --> 00:06:24.930 align:middle line:84%
the Grotto, which is an
underground cave system.

00:06:24.930 --> 00:06:27.810 align:middle line:10%
After we came up,
the representative

00:06:27.810 --> 00:06:30.090 align:middle line:10%
from the office of
tourism asked us

00:06:30.090 --> 00:06:32.460 align:middle line:10%
if we were interested
in seeing the dungeons

00:06:32.460 --> 00:06:35.520 align:middle line:10%
where the Templars were
housed when they were

00:06:35.520 --> 00:06:37.440 align:middle line:10%
held by King Philip the Fair.

00:06:37.440 --> 00:06:39.570 align:middle line:10%
So he walked us over
there, gave me the key,

00:06:39.570 --> 00:06:42.390 align:middle line:10%
and said that we could spend
as much time as we liked.

00:06:42.390 --> 00:06:44.160 align:middle line:10%
And so I photographed
everything.

00:06:44.160 --> 00:06:46.410 align:middle line:90%
[CAMERA CLICKING]

00:06:46.410 --> 00:06:49.080 align:middle line:84%
I photographed all the
crosses and the graffiti

00:06:49.080 --> 00:06:51.790 align:middle line:84%
and just spent about
an hour in the space.

00:06:51.790 --> 00:06:55.050 align:middle line:84%
So when we were done, I took the
key back to the representative

00:06:55.050 --> 00:07:00.022 align:middle line:84%
there and asked him who actually
carved the glyphs there.

00:07:00.022 --> 00:07:01.980 align:middle line:84%
And he said that they
were done by the Templars

00:07:01.980 --> 00:07:04.620 align:middle line:84%
while they were
awaiting their death.

00:07:04.620 --> 00:07:06.960 align:middle line:84%
And I asked him, well,
what do these symbols mean?

00:07:06.960 --> 00:07:10.110 align:middle line:84%
There was a lot
of small figures--

00:07:10.110 --> 00:07:12.930 align:middle line:84%
men, male figures, it
appeared to be, with crosses

00:07:12.930 --> 00:07:16.260 align:middle line:84%
above their heads, and just
several crosses throughout,

00:07:16.260 --> 00:07:17.400 align:middle line:90%
all over on the walls.

00:07:17.400 --> 00:07:21.360 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well, the Templars
were a religious order,

00:07:21.360 --> 00:07:24.660 align:middle line:84%
and he believed them
to be religious glyphs.

00:07:24.660 --> 00:07:29.190 align:middle line:84%
And I had no idea that
six years later, in 2015,

00:07:29.190 --> 00:07:32.475 align:middle line:84%
that I was going to be traveling
to Brazil and find a cave--

00:07:32.475 --> 00:07:33.300 align:middle line:90%
>> Woo!

00:07:33.300 --> 00:07:37.015 align:middle line:84%
>> --with a cross that was very
similar to these that I found

00:07:37.015 --> 00:07:37.815 align:middle line:90%
in Domme, France.

00:07:37.815 --> 00:07:41.528 align:middle line:90%


00:07:41.528 --> 00:07:44.000 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.410 align:middle line:84%
Seven years later, as she
leaves Brazil in 2015,

00:07:48.410 --> 00:07:52.250 align:middle line:84%
questions flood Kathleen's
mind about the relationship

00:07:52.250 --> 00:07:57.900 align:middle line:84%
between the glyphs in France
and the carving in Brazil.

00:07:57.900 --> 00:08:00.750 align:middle line:10%
What she already knows is this--

00:08:00.750 --> 00:08:04.140 align:middle line:10%
several hundred Templars,
including their grand master,

00:08:04.140 --> 00:08:08.100 align:middle line:10%
Jacques de Molay, were
imprisoned and murdered,

00:08:08.100 --> 00:08:11.010 align:middle line:10%
many in Domme itself.

00:08:11.010 --> 00:08:13.740 align:middle line:84%
This, combined with
the earlier fall

00:08:13.740 --> 00:08:17.940 align:middle line:84%
of their stronghold of Acre
in the Holy Land and abolition

00:08:17.940 --> 00:08:21.300 align:middle line:84%
of their order by
papal bull in 1312,

00:08:21.300 --> 00:08:26.480 align:middle line:84%
led the surviving Templars
to take drastic measures.

00:08:26.480 --> 00:08:29.900 align:middle line:84%
These seismic events
forced the Templars

00:08:29.900 --> 00:08:32.000 align:middle line:84%
to seek a place where
they could carry out

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:34.770 align:middle line:90%
their mission in safety.

00:08:34.770 --> 00:08:39.919 align:middle line:84%
So they reorganized
themselves in Portugal.

00:08:39.919 --> 00:08:41.780 align:middle line:84%
But might some
Templars have found

00:08:41.780 --> 00:08:46.170 align:middle line:84%
it necessary to leave
Europe entirely?

00:08:46.170 --> 00:08:49.320 align:middle line:84%
>> They had gone as far West
as they could in Europe.

00:08:49.320 --> 00:08:52.000 align:middle line:84%
There was nowhere
else to go but water.

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:55.620 align:middle line:10%
And one of the main reasons
that I think they left so early

00:08:55.620 --> 00:08:58.440 align:middle line:10%
was that they were
maybe even somewhat

00:08:58.440 --> 00:09:02.160 align:middle line:10%
desperate to recreate what
they'd created in Portugal,

00:09:02.160 --> 00:09:07.080 align:middle line:10%
which they could see was going
to be destroyed at some point.

00:09:07.080 --> 00:09:08.520 align:middle line:90%
The church was coming in.

00:09:08.520 --> 00:09:11.040 align:middle line:84%
They had threatened all
the other monarchies

00:09:11.040 --> 00:09:14.820 align:middle line:84%
throughout Europe that if they
didn't disband the Templars

00:09:14.820 --> 00:09:16.350 align:middle line:84%
and didn't take
their properties,

00:09:16.350 --> 00:09:17.970 align:middle line:90%
they would be excommunicated.

00:09:17.970 --> 00:09:20.110 align:middle line:84%
There was a tremendous
amount of pressure.

00:09:20.110 --> 00:09:21.120 align:middle line:90%
And so what did they do?

00:09:21.120 --> 00:09:25.110 align:middle line:10%
I believe, at that time, with
the blessing of King Denis,

00:09:25.110 --> 00:09:27.463 align:middle line:10%
I believe that they
left Portugal--

00:09:27.463 --> 00:09:29.880 align:middle line:10%
they had the fleets, they had
the money, they had the men,

00:09:29.880 --> 00:09:32.340 align:middle line:10%
and they certainly
had the motivation--

00:09:32.340 --> 00:09:36.600 align:middle line:10%
left to Brazil and colonized
the area in Alto Paraíso,

00:09:36.600 --> 00:09:38.940 align:middle line:10%
which is where I found the cave.

00:09:38.940 --> 00:09:42.300 align:middle line:84%
>> Could they have departed
from Portugal and made their way

00:09:42.300 --> 00:09:46.320 align:middle line:84%
to South America and to that
tiny cave outside of Alto

00:09:46.320 --> 00:09:47.940 align:middle line:90%
Paraíso?

00:09:47.940 --> 00:09:52.410 align:middle line:90%
And if so, how did they do it?

00:09:52.410 --> 00:09:53.940 align:middle line:84%
>> While they were
in the Holy Land,

00:09:53.940 --> 00:09:56.760 align:middle line:84%
there is a great deal of
speculation that they had

00:09:56.760 --> 00:10:01.770 align:middle line:84%
obtained the maps, boat-building
skills, to be able to travel.

00:10:01.770 --> 00:10:05.040 align:middle line:84%
And I believe that it was
at this time, some time

00:10:05.040 --> 00:10:10.590 align:middle line:84%
in, possibly, even, the
late 1200s and early 1300s,

00:10:10.590 --> 00:10:14.790 align:middle line:84%
that they took off and
traveled to South America.

00:10:14.790 --> 00:10:17.280 align:middle line:84%
>> Before exploring the
possibility of the Knights

00:10:17.280 --> 00:10:21.180 align:middle line:84%
Templar reaching Brazil, it
would be useful to know when

00:10:21.180 --> 00:10:25.000 align:middle line:90%
and why the order was created.

00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:28.290 align:middle line:84%
However, as is often the
case with the Templars,

00:10:28.290 --> 00:10:31.950 align:middle line:84%
even the most basic details
of the order's foundation

00:10:31.950 --> 00:10:33.120 align:middle line:90%
are shrouded in mystery.

00:10:33.120 --> 00:10:38.370 align:middle line:90%


00:10:38.370 --> 00:10:41.856 align:middle line:90%
[INTENSE MUSIC]

00:10:41.856 --> 00:10:49.824 align:middle line:90%


00:10:49.824 --> 00:10:53.310 align:middle line:90%
[VOCALIZING]

00:10:53.310 --> 00:11:40.710 align:middle line:90%


00:11:40.710 --> 00:11:44.310 align:middle line:84%
>> It's difficult for historians
either to determine the exact

00:11:44.310 --> 00:11:49.530 align:middle line:84%
date that the order was created
or to establish the true reason

00:11:49.530 --> 00:11:50.760 align:middle line:90%
for its coming into being.

00:11:50.760 --> 00:11:53.290 align:middle line:90%


00:11:53.290 --> 00:11:55.630 align:middle line:84%
One version of
their founding holds

00:11:55.630 --> 00:11:57.460 align:middle line:84%
that the Knights
Templar were established

00:11:57.460 --> 00:12:01.960 align:middle line:90%
in 1118 by Pope Urban II.

00:12:01.960 --> 00:12:04.510 align:middle line:84%
Their mission was
to protect pilgrims

00:12:04.510 --> 00:12:07.280 align:middle line:90%
traveling to the Holy Land.

00:12:07.280 --> 00:12:12.470 align:middle line:84%
>> Officially, it was created in
1118 and sanctioned by the pope

00:12:12.470 --> 00:12:14.690 align:middle line:90%
in 1139 AD.

00:12:14.690 --> 00:12:19.040 align:middle line:84%
Why they were created
is, wow, there's

00:12:19.040 --> 00:12:21.590 align:middle line:84%
a great deal of speculation
surrounding that.

00:12:21.590 --> 00:12:24.530 align:middle line:84%
The accepted reason
that they were created

00:12:24.530 --> 00:12:27.530 align:middle line:84%
was to accompany
pilgrims to the Holy Land

00:12:27.530 --> 00:12:30.420 align:middle line:84%
and also to fight
in the Crusades.

00:12:30.420 --> 00:12:33.170 align:middle line:84%
However, it doesn't
seem very likely

00:12:33.170 --> 00:12:35.570 align:middle line:84%
that they were going
to be able to fend off

00:12:35.570 --> 00:12:38.360 align:middle line:84%
enemies that were trying to
kill thousands of pilgrims.

00:12:38.360 --> 00:12:40.080 align:middle line:84%
It just doesn't
seem very likely.

00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:41.660 align:middle line:84%
My belief is that
they were there

00:12:41.660 --> 00:12:45.020 align:middle line:84%
to excavate under the temple,
under the stables, which

00:12:45.020 --> 00:12:47.280 align:middle line:84%
is where they were
given that property.

00:12:47.280 --> 00:12:49.850 align:middle line:84%
And this is where they built
their stronghold while they

00:12:49.850 --> 00:12:51.200 align:middle line:90%
were there in the Holy Land.

00:12:51.200 --> 00:12:54.620 align:middle line:84%
It was right above
the Temple Mount.

00:12:54.620 --> 00:12:57.710 align:middle line:10%
>> Yet documents from the
time indicate that the order

00:12:57.710 --> 00:13:01.390 align:middle line:10%
consisted of just 11 Knights.

00:13:01.390 --> 00:13:04.060 align:middle line:84%
The notion that such a
small group of individuals

00:13:04.060 --> 00:13:08.110 align:middle line:84%
would be tasked with protecting
thousands of pilgrims

00:13:08.110 --> 00:13:10.540 align:middle line:90%
strikes many today as unlikely.

00:13:10.540 --> 00:13:14.140 align:middle line:90%


00:13:14.140 --> 00:13:17.890 align:middle line:84%
>> After the First Crusade
was launched in 1096,

00:13:17.890 --> 00:13:21.280 align:middle line:84%
the Frenchman Godfrey de
Bouillon and many other knights

00:13:21.280 --> 00:13:24.400 align:middle line:84%
defended Christendom
by attacking the Turks

00:13:24.400 --> 00:13:27.550 align:middle line:90%
in Constantinople and Anatolia.

00:13:27.550 --> 00:13:31.820 align:middle line:84%
Three years later, they
achieved their major aim,

00:13:31.820 --> 00:13:38.400 align:middle line:84%
the recapture of the Holy
City of Jerusalem in 1099.

00:13:38.400 --> 00:13:41.850 align:middle line:84%
So were they the
original Templars?

00:13:41.850 --> 00:13:45.030 align:middle line:84%
Whatever the circumstances
of the order's founding,

00:13:45.030 --> 00:13:47.580 align:middle line:84%
by the 12th century,
the Knights Templar

00:13:47.580 --> 00:13:50.070 align:middle line:90%
were present in the Holy Land.

00:13:50.070 --> 00:13:53.430 align:middle line:10%
Their task was to defend
it for the Church of Rome.

00:13:53.430 --> 00:13:58.280 align:middle line:90%


00:13:58.280 --> 00:14:00.710 align:middle line:10%
The new order of
the Knights Templar

00:14:00.710 --> 00:14:04.580 align:middle line:10%
was quartered in Jerusalem
in part of the Temple Mount,

00:14:04.580 --> 00:14:06.680 align:middle line:10%
directly above
what were believed

00:14:06.680 --> 00:14:12.590 align:middle line:10%
to be the buried remains of King
Solomon's temple and stables.

00:14:12.590 --> 00:14:16.400 align:middle line:84%
There, it is believed that
they discovered holy relics

00:14:16.400 --> 00:14:18.620 align:middle line:90%
and scrolls.

00:14:18.620 --> 00:14:22.130 align:middle line:84%
These significantly
and permanently shifted

00:14:22.130 --> 00:14:25.460 align:middle line:84%
the trajectory of the
order and greatly increased

00:14:25.460 --> 00:14:27.590 align:middle line:90%
its importance.

00:14:27.590 --> 00:14:33.810 align:middle line:84%
The exact nature of what
they found remains a mystery.

00:14:33.810 --> 00:14:36.800 align:middle line:10%
But the actions of the Templars
in the immediate aftermath

00:14:36.800 --> 00:14:40.500 align:middle line:10%
of their discoveries
make a fascinating story,

00:14:40.500 --> 00:14:42.800 align:middle line:10%
which is brought to
light in numerous books

00:14:42.800 --> 00:14:47.210 align:middle line:10%
by the author and
historian Freddy Silva.

00:14:47.210 --> 00:14:50.450 align:middle line:10%
>> They already had the people
in place with which to set up

00:14:50.450 --> 00:14:54.230 align:middle line:10%
a framework with which they
could set up a secular state.

00:14:54.230 --> 00:14:57.230 align:middle line:84%
And their benefactor, who
was Bernard of Clairvaux,

00:14:57.230 --> 00:15:00.050 align:middle line:84%
the centerpiece of the
Templars, was the head

00:15:00.050 --> 00:15:01.940 align:middle line:90%
of the Cistercian order.

00:15:01.940 --> 00:15:04.410 align:middle line:84%
If you understand
where he came from,

00:15:04.410 --> 00:15:07.280 align:middle line:84%
he was also looking to create
a kingdom of conscience

00:15:07.280 --> 00:15:10.160 align:middle line:84%
in a part of Europe, something
that had not been corrupted

00:15:10.160 --> 00:15:12.260 align:middle line:90%
by the Catholic belief system.

00:15:12.260 --> 00:15:15.290 align:middle line:84%
He wanted an original
form of Christianity

00:15:15.290 --> 00:15:17.630 align:middle line:84%
to be founded on the
principles that were set up

00:15:17.630 --> 00:15:20.000 align:middle line:84%
in the days when Jesus
and his disciples

00:15:20.000 --> 00:15:23.060 align:middle line:84%
were around and yet
almost different to what

00:15:23.060 --> 00:15:25.580 align:middle line:84%
they were practicing, almost
like a Buddhist ideal.

00:15:25.580 --> 00:15:28.640 align:middle line:84%
So the Templars found themselves
in this unique opportunity

00:15:28.640 --> 00:15:31.280 align:middle line:84%
where they had a brand new
piece of real estate with which

00:15:31.280 --> 00:15:33.620 align:middle line:84%
to operate from
scratch and set out

00:15:33.620 --> 00:15:38.220 align:middle line:84%
their dogma in complete
freedom, away from the church.

00:15:38.220 --> 00:15:42.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Silva describes the Templars'
deliberate and focused creation

00:15:42.360 --> 00:15:46.110 align:middle line:84%
of a sovereign nation,
the kingdom of Portugal,

00:15:46.110 --> 00:15:48.880 align:middle line:90%
created in 1139.

00:15:48.880 --> 00:15:52.090 align:middle line:84%
He also cites documentation
and local stories

00:15:52.090 --> 00:15:56.590 align:middle line:84%
passed down through generations
in France, Italy, Spain,

00:15:56.590 --> 00:16:00.360 align:middle line:90%
Scotland, and Portugal itself.

00:16:00.360 --> 00:16:04.020 align:middle line:84%
This evidence supports the
claim that the Templars

00:16:04.020 --> 00:16:09.870 align:middle line:84%
sought to protect the bloodline
of Jesus and Mary Magdalene.

00:16:09.870 --> 00:16:12.840 align:middle line:84%
The Templars' ideal
nation was to be

00:16:12.840 --> 00:16:17.490 align:middle line:84%
one governed by the
descendants of this bloodline.

00:16:17.490 --> 00:16:19.950 align:middle line:84%
It would include
and welcome people

00:16:19.950 --> 00:16:22.740 align:middle line:84%
of all religious
and cultural beliefs

00:16:22.740 --> 00:16:26.070 align:middle line:84%
and of all social and
economic backgrounds.

00:16:26.070 --> 00:16:29.670 align:middle line:84%
>> They wanted to have a
sovereign nation where people

00:16:29.670 --> 00:16:34.020 align:middle line:84%
could come and
bring about harmony.

00:16:34.020 --> 00:16:37.350 align:middle line:84%
And it was the only
country in all of Europe

00:16:37.350 --> 00:16:39.150 align:middle line:90%
that this was happening.

00:16:39.150 --> 00:16:43.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Such theories correspond
with well-documented records

00:16:43.320 --> 00:16:47.490 align:middle line:84%
of the Templars protecting
Jews and those Christians that

00:16:47.490 --> 00:16:51.180 align:middle line:84%
the church considered
heretics, such as the Gnostics

00:16:51.180 --> 00:16:53.640 align:middle line:90%
and the Cathars.

00:16:53.640 --> 00:16:58.200 align:middle line:10%
It's a historical fact that many
members of these groups fleeing

00:16:58.200 --> 00:17:01.140 align:middle line:10%
the onslaught of
the Holy Inquisition

00:17:01.140 --> 00:17:03.285 align:middle line:10%
were given sanctuary
in Portugal.

00:17:03.285 --> 00:17:09.579 align:middle line:90%


00:17:09.579 --> 00:17:11.650 align:middle line:84%
The primary headquarters
of the Templars

00:17:11.650 --> 00:17:15.384 align:middle line:84%
was thought to be in France,
where grand master Jacques de

00:17:15.384 --> 00:17:18.069 align:middle line:84%
Molay and several
thousand other Templars

00:17:18.069 --> 00:17:21.230 align:middle line:90%
resided prior to their capture.

00:17:21.230 --> 00:17:25.490 align:middle line:84%
But Silva convincingly argues
that the Templars actually had

00:17:25.490 --> 00:17:29.600 align:middle line:90%
several strongholds in Europe.

00:17:29.600 --> 00:17:32.420 align:middle line:84%
At this time, King
Philip IV of France

00:17:32.420 --> 00:17:36.502 align:middle line:84%
desperately needed to
replenish his depleted coffers.

00:17:36.502 --> 00:17:39.710 align:middle line:84%
He had already rounded
up and murdered the Jews,

00:17:39.710 --> 00:17:42.410 align:middle line:84%
confiscating all
of their property.

00:17:42.410 --> 00:17:45.680 align:middle line:84%
But he was also in
great financial debt

00:17:45.680 --> 00:17:52.400 align:middle line:84%
to the Templars, a debt that
he wished to avoid paying.

00:17:52.400 --> 00:17:58.490 align:middle line:84%
On Friday the 13th, 1307, he
moved against the Templars,

00:17:58.490 --> 00:18:02.300 align:middle line:84%
arresting them and confiscating
all of their wealth and lands

00:18:02.300 --> 00:18:04.460 align:middle line:90%
in France.

00:18:04.460 --> 00:18:07.490 align:middle line:84%
The fact that many Templars
who escaped Philip's wrath

00:18:07.490 --> 00:18:11.960 align:middle line:84%
fled to Portugal, which had
also welcomed the Jews, Cathars,

00:18:11.960 --> 00:18:17.060 align:middle line:84%
and Gnostics, suggests that the
Templars held vast lands there,

00:18:17.060 --> 00:18:17.860 align:middle line:90%
as well.

00:18:17.860 --> 00:18:20.850 align:middle line:90%


00:18:20.850 --> 00:18:23.630 align:middle line:84%
It was possible that
the city of Tomar

00:18:23.630 --> 00:18:27.420 align:middle line:84%
became a major
stronghold for them.

00:18:27.420 --> 00:18:31.070 align:middle line:84%
But how many Templars
actually resided in Tomar?

00:18:31.070 --> 00:18:33.890 align:middle line:84%
And would they have been
able to gather a fleet

00:18:33.890 --> 00:18:36.680 align:middle line:84%
to travel by sea from
their port to Brazil?

00:18:36.680 --> 00:18:41.270 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:18:41.270 --> 00:18:44.720 align:middle line:84%
We know from history that the
Templars gave refuge to peoples

00:18:44.720 --> 00:18:47.600 align:middle line:84%
from all nationalities
and religious backgrounds,

00:18:47.600 --> 00:18:50.930 align:middle line:84%
such as the Jews,
Cathars, and Gnostics,

00:18:50.930 --> 00:18:53.780 align:middle line:84%
who were fleeing
persecution from the church.

00:18:53.780 --> 00:18:57.410 align:middle line:84%
>> You have to understand
that during the 1300s,

00:18:57.410 --> 00:19:01.310 align:middle line:84%
that the church dominated the
entire continent of Europe.

00:19:01.310 --> 00:19:04.400 align:middle line:84%
You couldn't do anything without
permission from the church.

00:19:04.400 --> 00:19:06.920 align:middle line:10%
And Portugal was a holdout.

00:19:06.920 --> 00:19:09.680 align:middle line:10%
Portugal was the
only country that

00:19:09.680 --> 00:19:16.550 align:middle line:10%
