00:22:16.070 --> 00:22:19.190 align:middle line:84%
>> While following the trail of
the Templars from Brazil back

00:22:19.190 --> 00:22:24.170 align:middle line:84%
to Portugal, Kathleen
visits the city of Tomar.

00:22:24.170 --> 00:22:26.990 align:middle line:84%
The city was founded by
the Templars themselves

00:22:26.990 --> 00:22:30.050 align:middle line:84%
and was their
headquarters in Portugal.

00:22:30.050 --> 00:22:32.450 align:middle line:84%
Dating back to the
early 12th century

00:22:32.450 --> 00:22:35.150 align:middle line:84%
and still standing
in Tomar today

00:22:35.150 --> 00:22:37.820 align:middle line:84%
are a Templar
castle and churches

00:22:37.820 --> 00:22:41.990 align:middle line:84%
dedicated to John the
Baptist and Mary Magdalene.

00:22:41.990 --> 00:22:46.010 align:middle line:84%
Here, many of the orders'
early grand masters

00:22:46.010 --> 00:22:49.570 align:middle line:90%
were laid to rest.

00:22:49.570 --> 00:22:54.160 align:middle line:84%
In Tomar, Kathleen is introduced
to Joao Fiandeiro, who

00:22:54.160 --> 00:22:56.540 align:middle line:84%
is a current Templar
and a researcher

00:22:56.540 --> 00:22:59.170 align:middle line:90%
and expert on Templar crosses.

00:22:59.170 --> 00:23:02.050 align:middle line:84%
He provides her with information
about the Templar's role

00:23:02.050 --> 00:23:05.200 align:middle line:84%
in founding Portugal
and their goal

00:23:05.200 --> 00:23:08.890 align:middle line:84%
of protecting the royal
bloodline of Jesus and Mary

00:23:08.890 --> 00:23:09.798 align:middle line:90%
Magdalene.

00:23:09.798 --> 00:23:12.530 align:middle line:90%


00:23:12.530 --> 00:23:14.530 align:middle line:84%
>> What was the Templars'
relationship with Mary

00:23:14.530 --> 00:23:16.150 align:middle line:90%
Magdalene?

00:23:16.150 --> 00:23:19.420 align:middle line:84%
Was there a secret or
anything that they may

00:23:19.420 --> 00:23:21.940 align:middle line:90%
have been trying to protect?

00:23:21.940 --> 00:23:27.690 align:middle line:10%
>> The Templar Knights were
very Marian in their worships.

00:23:27.690 --> 00:23:33.560 align:middle line:10%
They were worshipping Mary,
the mother, and, of course,

00:23:33.560 --> 00:23:36.610 align:middle line:10%
what it represents,
not just the mother

00:23:36.610 --> 00:23:39.410 align:middle line:10%
of Christ but the mother--

00:23:39.410 --> 00:23:42.230 align:middle line:10%
the mother of all of us.

00:23:42.230 --> 00:23:48.160 align:middle line:84%
Templar Knights has
mentor St. John Baptist.

00:23:48.160 --> 00:23:52.750 align:middle line:84%
Because for them, that's the
man that baptized Christ.

00:23:52.750 --> 00:23:56.650 align:middle line:84%
So that's the man that
started the Christianism.

00:23:56.650 --> 00:24:02.170 align:middle line:84%
For them, he's the one that
is the mentor of Christians.

00:24:02.170 --> 00:24:08.440 align:middle line:84%
But it's from the Mary, the
mother, that life comes.

00:24:08.440 --> 00:24:12.160 align:middle line:84%
And being that, as a ritual
for the Templar Knights,

00:24:12.160 --> 00:24:16.150 align:middle line:84%
and they use that in a
lot of their symbolism,

00:24:16.150 --> 00:24:22.390 align:middle line:84%
it gives us that clue that they
might be protecting something

00:24:22.390 --> 00:24:27.260 align:middle line:84%
more than just the physical
mother that we have

00:24:27.260 --> 00:24:34.195 align:middle line:84%
but the mother of the one
that was really the Christ.

00:24:34.195 --> 00:24:41.980 align:middle line:84%
And too, that bloodline
that might have existed,

00:24:41.980 --> 00:24:45.430 align:middle line:84%
probably the Templar Knights
have been their protectors,

00:24:45.430 --> 00:24:51.340 align:middle line:84%
and they had that knowledge
about Mary Magdalene.

00:24:51.340 --> 00:24:54.580 align:middle line:84%
>> But learning all of these
historical details leaves

00:24:54.580 --> 00:24:56.640 align:middle line:90%
Kathleen puzzled.

00:24:56.640 --> 00:24:59.610 align:middle line:10%
Having gone to the trouble
and hard work of establishing

00:24:59.610 --> 00:25:03.930 align:middle line:10%
Portugal as a nation founded
on their beliefs and goals,

00:25:03.930 --> 00:25:06.900 align:middle line:10%
why did the Templars flee?

00:25:06.900 --> 00:25:09.209 align:middle line:90%
And where did they go?

00:25:09.209 --> 00:25:12.143 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:25:12.143 --> 00:25:17.530 align:middle line:90%


